+# CTO Incident - phase 7.10.z autonomy backlog block
+
+Saved: 2026-05-08T02:14:30Z. Role: codex-cto-remediation-FR.
+
+## Classification
+
+Infra-only, still valid.
+
+The active block is not a scientific-result rejection. The blocked work only
+adds six autonomy backlog BRIEFs, and the worker recorded green brief-gate
+validation. The block remains valid because the blocked branch is still
+non-linear against current `origin/main`, no recovery branch has recorded
+`CTO_UNBLOCK.md`, and the chef fast-forward-only gate has not been re-proven.
+
+## Active Block
+
+- Block file:
+  `outbox/_blocks/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z.block`
+- Blocked phase:
+  `phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z`
+- Block text: created `2026-05-08T02:04:38+02:00`, panel average `81`,
+  advisor `BLOCK`, email queued, chef paused.
+- Matching artifacts read:
+  `CHEF_VERDICT.md`, `PANEL_CHECK.md`, `SUMMARY.md`, `KAIZEN.md`, and
+  `run.log.tail`.
+- Advisor artifact:
+  `outbox/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z/ADVISOR_CHECK.md`
+  is absent. The block file says advisor `BLOCK`; the chef log records advisor
+  Codex exit non-zero before block creation. Treat this as a fail-closed
+  artifact gap, not as unblock evidence.
+
+## Root Cause
+
+The worker completed and pushed commit
+`f2fbb3f830ed197e904b5a45d62bc64f79d500b3` on
+`origin/phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T235013Z`, but that
+branch was based on stale merge base `dd906caaba88a4bc81978bac52370a603484549f`.
+Current remote `main` is `7a655337908a0ba7aff623d51707750c07fbc648`.
+
+Chef attempted the configured fast-forward merge path and correctly aborted
+because `origin/main` is not an ancestor of the blocked branch and the blocked
+branch is not an ancestor of `origin/main`. The panel correctly treated this as
+a source-of-truth and chef-reproducibility failure. The smaller process bug is
+that worker-side success did not prove branch freshness after push.
+
+Secondary operational evidence: worker and chef logs show intermittent fresh
+`.git/index.lock` contention in `/mnt/c/doctorat/bsebench-org/bsebench-async-codex`.
+The direct check at `2026-05-08T02:13Z` found no persistent lock, so the live
+unblock gate is branch lineage plus a recorded recovery proof, not lock removal.
+
+## Blast Radius
+
+- One active block pauses the chef-daemon by design.
+- Normal scientific queueing is paused while the block exists; the pacer is
+  only queuing bounded block-remediation tasks during its cooldown window.
+- Worker daemons, the chef daemon, and the CTO daemon are alive, but daemon
+  liveness does not clear the chef-side mergeability failure.
+- Watchdog state shows the same block across `bsebench-async-codex`,
+  `bsebench-async-codex-worker-2`, and `bsebench-async-codex-cto-report`.
+- Two stale `running` statuses are still reported by watchdog:
+  `phase-7-10-l-stats-hinf-fragility-threshold-calibration` and
+  `phase-7-10-z-autonomy-backlog-replenishment-20260507T193014Z`.
+- This incident response did not edit thesis files, claim registry files,
+  `claims/registry.yaml`, `claim_55`, roadmap files, source ledgers, or
+  scientific claim text.
+
+## Current Evidence
+
+- `CHEF_VERDICT.md` records decision `escalated` and
